HEADWORD: Spoffish
<hw>Spof"fish</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ocr⟧f"f⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Probably from Prov. E. <ets>spoffle</ets> to be spoffish.]</ety>
<def>Earnest and active in matters of no moment; bustling.</def>
